@Component is a generic stereotype annotation used to register a class as a Spring bean in the application context.

@Service and @Repository are specialized forms of @Component.


@Service is used at the business logic layer, where core application logic and validations are implemented.

@Repository is used at the data access layer to interact with the database and perform CRUD operations.

Internally, all three annotations work the same because they are meta-annotated with @Component. However, @Repository provides additional functionality such as automatic exception translation of database exceptions into Spring’s DataAccessException.”